#: qml/ConfigGeneral.qml:174
#, kde-kuit-format
msgctxt "@info:usagetip"
msgid ""
"Look for a setting in <application>%1</application> to disable its tray icon "
"before doing it here. Some apps’ tray icons were not designed to be "
"disabled, and using this setting may cause them to behave unexpectedly.<nl/"
"><nl/>Use this setting at your own risk, and do not report issues to KDE or "
"the app’s author."
msgstr ""

#: qml/ConfigGeneral.qml:177
#, kde-format
msgctxt "@action:button"
msgid "I understand the risks"
msgstr ""

#: qml/ConfigGeneral.qml:189
#, kde-kuit-format
msgctxt "@info:usagetip"
msgid ""
"Disabling the clipboard is not recommended, as it will cause copied data to "
"be lost when the application it was copied from is closed.<nl/><nl/>Only do "
"this if you’ve manually added a standalone Clipboard widget somewhere else, "
"or are using a 3rd-party clipboard manager. Also, instead consider "
"configuring the clipboard to not save history, or to only remember one item "
"at a time."
msgstr ""

#: qml/ConfigGeneral.qml:198
#, kde-kuit-format
msgctxt "@info:usagetip"
msgid ""
"Disabling the Notifications widget is not recommended, as notifications sent "
"by apps will no longer be shown.<nl/><nl/>Only do this if you’ve manually "
"added a standalone Notifications widget somewhere else, or are intentionally "
"using a 3rd-party notification manager to handle notifications."
msgstr ""

